#Installing Django!#

https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.5/intro/install/

Download it:
https://www.djangoproject.com/download/

I liked Option 2, without the package manager getting involved.
(though it turns out, OS X comes with easy_install. So I could've just 
used that)

But I ROUGHED IT!

tar xzvf Django-1.6b2.tar.gz
cd Django-1.6b2
sudo python setup.py install

After all that, test to see it worked:
$ cmdprompt> python
>>> import django
>>> print(django.get_version())
1.5

Or, you can check to see if it worked with this: 

python -c "import django; print(django.get_version())"


#MAking your first site#

https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.5/intro/tutorial01/

Run this!
django-admin.py startproject mysite



